<DOC><DOCNO> AP880325-0259 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-25-88 1105EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-Bruno's-PigglyWiggly     03-25 0140</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bruno's-Piggly Wiggly,0146</SECOND><HEAD>Grocery Chain Buys Piggly Wiggly Stores</HEAD><DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bruno's Inc., Alabama's largest grocerychain, has agreed to buy 82 Piggly Wiggly stores in Georgia for $30million in stock, company officials said.   Bruno's, a Birmingham-based company, already has 123supermarkets. Under the agreement, Bruno's will buy Piggly WigglySouthern, a Vidalia holding company that owns stores in central andsouthern Georgia.   The purchase, announced Thursday, includes a 585,000-square-footwarehouse in Vidalia that serves all 82 stores.   Bruno's operates supermarkets under the names of Bruno's, FoodWorld, Foodmax and Consumer Warehouse Foods in Alabama, Georgia,Tennessee and Florida. With the addition of the Piggly Wigglystores, it will have more than 200 stores.   The Georgia stores that Bruno's plans to buy will continue tooperate under the Piggly Wiggly name, said Bruno's spokeswoman BethDunnaway.</TEXT></DOC>